track_notes: This route may seem a bit longer, but I found it to be vastly better than the more direct route (see DOWN route).  The hike across the desert is straightforward, with no significant washes to traverse.  After a relatively fast 3.4 miles, turn east headed up a broad wash.  I’m not sure that I picked the best route up the broad wash; feel free to deviate – but stay in the wash.  At an elevation of 3320 ft you’ll leave the wash and strike directly uphill.  Be forewarned:  the footing is NOT good on this uphill.  Thankfully this pitch is short, about 0.3 miles, and you’ll find yourself on the top – which is a very welcome mesa!  Plenty of room on the summit.  In Oct 2019 there was a hefty wooden stake in the center of a 4-ft cairn on the summit – the wooden stake worked nicely to secure an antenna mast. There was a sturdy ammo can for a climber’s log.  While this route might’ve seemed challenging when you get to the top, it’s a CAKEWALK compared to the alternate route going down!!!  de K7Z

I’ll start and end these notes with the same RECOMMENDATION TO NOT USE THIS ROUTE!!  This route was posted on a climbing website, and vying for some diversity in the day I decided to give it a whirl.  Necessitated by the route, the top section does not consistently or intuitively follow any topography.  It varies from going down a wash, to crossing ridges, and then crossing more ridges.  Careful attention to your GPS is warranted (if you examine my path closely, you’ll see I did NOT exactly follow the previously-published route on the top section.  The bottom section follows a wash.  Thankfully this wash is largely devoid of vegetation.  HOWEVER, there are many, many sections which require great care.  Including a 15-ft dry waterfall which must be circumvented to the west.  Granted, I was a bit tired from the ascent, but so much care was required that any sense of this route being shorter is completely negated by the slow rate of descent.  I DO NOT RECOMMEND THIS ROUTE.   de K7ZOO
track_title: Hike DOWN 2019 10 25 - THIS ROUTE NOT RECOMMENDED
